    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21"
                            >Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Omnibus sanctae Dei Ecclesiae fidelibus
                        nostrisque presentibus scilicet et futuris notum esse volumus, qualiter
                            <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops" ref="#people/123"
                            >Adelardus</persName> et <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops"><name
                                ref="Antonius">Antonius</name></persName> venerabiles <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> atque <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Marquis/duke"><name ref="Uualdefredus"
                                >Vualfredus</name></persName> illuster <rs key="#Marquis/duke"
                            >marchio</rs> nostri dilectissimi <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideles</rs>
                        nostram humiliter postulaverunt <rs key="#Intercessory">clementiam</rs>,
                        quatenus <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/55">Angilbergae</persName>
                        serenissimae <rs key="#Queen">imperatrici</rs> concedere et confirmare
                        nostrae auctoritatis precepto dignaremur quandam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1503"><rs key="#Monasteries">abbatiam</rs> in
                            honore apostolorum principis dicatam</orgName> et non longe ab urbe
                            <placeName ref="#places/43">Placentina</placeName> fundatam in loco
                        nuncupato <placeName ref="#places/14"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            >Caput Trebie</placeName>, seu etiam quasdam <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >cortes</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/40"><placeName ref="#places/33"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Vuardistallam</placeName></geogName> videlicet, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/38"><placeName ref="#places/32"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Luciariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/77"><placeName ref="#places/361">Litora
                                Palludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/110"><placeName ref="#places/141"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Campum Miliacium</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/112"><placeName ref="#places/354"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Sextum</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/113"><placeName ref="#places/278"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Iverne</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/114"><placeName ref="#places/503"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Massini</placeName></geogName> atque <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/115"><placeName ref="#places/1908"
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                                >Leocarni</placeName></geogName> quemadmodum domnus <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/110">Hludovicus</persName> gloriosus
                        olim <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> avunculus et senior noster eidem
                        imperatrici per suorum <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">preceptorum
                            paginas</rs> concessit atque perdonavit. Quorum precibus inflexi
                        prenominatam abbatiam atque <rs key="#Royal_slave">familiis utriusque
                            sexus</rs> seu etiam quae dici aut nominari possunt per diversa nostri
                        regni loca ad pretaxatam abbatiam vel ad easdem cortes pertinentibus in
                        integrum, veluti prelibatus serenissimus imperator Hludovicus et quondam
                        noster avunculus nosterque carissimus senior <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/32">Karolus</persName> videlicet invictissimus imperator
                        per <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">preceptorum suorum</rs> auctoritatem
                        iam saepe nominatae Angilbergae gloriosae imperatrici tribuerunt ac
                        confirmaverunt. Nec non et omnia quae in aliis preceptis tam sibi quamque
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> in honore <orgName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Levies #Public_exactions #Profits_of_justice #Monasteries #Nuns/sanctimoniales #Aldius #Slave"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/53">sancti Sixti dicato</orgName> et ab ipsa
                        infra civitatem Placentinam constructo ab aliis nostris antecessoribus
                        donata et corroborata fuisse noscuntur. Nos ob Dei amorem tam ad utilitatem
                        ipsius Angilbergae imperatricis quamque ad usus et alimenta <rs
                            key="#Nuns/sanctimoniales">monacharum</rs> quae pro tempore in eodem
                        monasterio Christo domino servierint de nostro iure et dominio in ipsius
                        Angilbergae excellentissimae imperatricis et monasterii ius et dominium
                        usque <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">in perpetuum iure
                            peroprietario</rs> concedimus ac perdonamus, modisque omnibus
                        confirmamus et conroboramus per hanc nostrae inscriptionis paginam una cum
                        casis, terris, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>, pascuis, <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs>, salectis, sationibus, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque
                            decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, <rs key="#Slave">servis et ancillis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Aldius">aldionibus et aldianis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains"
                            >montibus</rs>, vallibus, planiciebus, coltis et incoltis, divisis et
                        indivisis, ripis, rupunis, <rs
                            key="#Levies #Public_exactions #Profits_of_justice">vestigalibus,
                            districtionibus, reddibitionibus</rs> universisque ad predictam abbatiam
                        vel iam nominatas cortes pertinentibus vel aspicientibus ex integro,
                        quatenus ipsa, quoad vixerit, eandem abbatiam et pretaxatas cortes
                        potestative teneat ac possideat et ordinet, totius potestatis contradictione
                        remota. Quicumque ergo hoc nostrae concessionis et confirmationis preceptum
                        infringere vel violare quandoque temptaverit, sciat se compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri obtimi libras centum sexaginta</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">medietatem palacii nostri camerae</rs> et medietatem
                        cui inuste facta fuerit molestia. Quod autem ut verius credatur et
                        diligentius ab omnibus perpetualiter observetur, manu propria roboantes de
                        anulo nostro subter insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Berengarii serenissimi
                        regis. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/123">Adelardi</persName>
                        episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et
                        subscripsi. Data VIII id. mai(i), anno incarnationis Domini DCCCLXXXVIII,
                        domni autem Berengarii gloriosissimi regis I, indictione VI actum Papie. In
                        Dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
